{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"48304e8e-242a-495a-9b19-468d192d5677","content":"**Yes, you will hit a compatibility issue.** MSTest v4 dropped support for `net6.0` and `net7.0`. Only `net8.0+`, `net462`, and `uap10.0` are supported.\n\nYou'll need to **retarget to `net8.0`** (or later) before upgrading to MSTest v4. For example:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\nYour test code itself (`SimpleTests.cs`) is simple and shouldn't need any changes — it uses basic `[TestClass]`/`[TestMethod]` attributes and `Assert.IsTrue`, which are fully compatible with v4.\n\n**Summary of required steps:**\n1. Change `net6.0` → `net8.0` in `TestProject.csproj`\n2. Upgrade `MSTest` from `3.8.0` → `4.x`\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"67ff15c6-8733-4fc5-869c-b40870809e21","outputTokens":233},"id":"6bcf14af-587a-40ed-963b-93313502b261","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:20:00.984Z","parentId":"a0f718bc-997c-40fd-a454-831629a12d70"}
